# The Joy of Movement – AI Content Creator

An AI-powered content creation system for **The Joy of Movement** — a German
community brand for people 55+. Built with Python and the Anthropic Claude API.

> "We don't build courses. We give people a new answer to the question:
> Who am I now — and with whom?"

---

## What This System Does

Takes brand documents and market research as input.
Produces authentic, identity-driven content as output.
Demonstrably different from generic AI-generated content.

**Content types:** Social media posts · Blog posts · Newsletters

**Pipeline:** Document → Monitor → Brief → Publish → Iterate

---

## Why It's Not AI-Slop

Generic ChatGPT output:
> "It's never too late to start your fitness journey! Join us and discover
> the power of movement! 💪 #ActiveAging #FitnessOver60"

This system's output:
> "Klaus turned 60 last month. For the first time in 40 years, nobody needed
> him to be anything. No job title. No role. Now there's a Tuesday.
> Eight people. The same eight people. They know when he's not there."

The difference is structural. Generic prompts produce generic outputs.
This system injects brand voice, competitor contrast, and market context
directly into every prompt — making replication without the knowledge base
impossible.

---

## Project Structure

```
joy-of-movement-content-creator/
├── src/
│   ├── document_processor.py   # Markdown ingestion and parsing
│   ├── knowledge_base.py       # KB management wrapper
│   ├── prompt_templates.py     # 3 prompt templates (Brand / Industry / Hybrid)
│   ├── content_pipeline.py     # Full pipeline orchestration
│   ├── llm_integration.py      # Anthropic Claude API integration
│   └── main.py                 # Interactive CLI entry point
├── knowledge_base/
│   ├── primary/                # Company-specific documents
│   │   ├── brand_guidelines.md
│   │   ├── product_specs.md
│   │   └── past_content/
│   │       └── example_post.md
│   └── secondary/              # Industry research
│       ├── market_trends.md
│       └── competitor_analysis.md
├── templates/
│   └── index.html              # Flask template (web app)
├── static/
│   ├── style.css               # Web app styling
│   └── script.js               # Web app frontend logic
├── output/                     # Generated content (auto-created)
├── config/
│   └── vscode_agent.json       # VSCode agent configuration
├── app.py                      # Flask web application
├── requirements.txt            # CLI dependencies
├── requirements-web.txt        # Web app dependencies
├── .env                        # API keys (not committed)
└── README
```
